  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They took us-- [CLEARS THROAT] the partisans, they took us to the board, to the old board, Poland and Germany and Russia-- to the, to the [? brook. ?] That's the river [? brook. ?] If we cannot come across the river to go in the back to the Germans, to fight them from the back.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We stay maybe a couple days, then it's they decided to send us, all the partisans, to send us in the Russian Army.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They give us the papers, they give us [? new, ?] where to go.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They send us [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That's, that was-- I didn't tell them about the [INAUDIBLE] we was together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that time, we divided.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He went in one place, they sent him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Maybe it was a mistake, our mistake, why we didn't go together to stay, to stay, to ask people to go together.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Or maybe it's another-- I don't know how, what is happening.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He, he was looking like for a Jew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I was looking, [? but ?] you cannot see.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "From outside, you cannot see what I am, what I am a Jew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they begin from the partisan, they begin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They send us an army to teach us for to be [RUSSIAN].",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That's mean to come to spy to the Germans to spy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And it was a special group in the army.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Most of them, they take partisans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "They take people what know don't have relatives, don't have nobody.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Why it was no [? deaths. ?] I didn't know in this time what [? became ?] after.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We understand why it [? was. ?] When they send the people that they send us, that's 95% we went what will be dead.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
